, pp. 75-91; Galvosas, P., Stallmach, F., Kärger, J., Background gradient suppression in stimulated echo NMR diffusion studies using magic pulsed field gradient ratios (2004) J. Magn. Reson., 166 (2), pp. 164-173; Tanner, J.E., Use of the stimulated echo in NMR diffusion studies (1970) J. Chem. Phys., 52, p. 2523; Codd, S.L., Altobelli, S.A., A PGSE study of propane gas flow through model porous bead packs (2003) J. Magn. Reson., 163 (1), pp. 16-22; Stallmach, F., Galvosas, P., Spin echo NMR diffusion studies (2007) Annu. Rep. NMR Spectrosc., 61, pp. 51-131. , Elsevier, Amsterdam, Boston, Heidelberg; Spindler, N., Pohlmeier, A., Galvosas, P., Water flow investigation on quartz sand with 13-interval stimulated echo multi-slice imaging (2011) AIP Conf. Proc., 1330 (1), pp. 73-76; Kandhai, D., Hlushkou, D., Hoekstra, A.G., Sloot, P.M.A., Van As, H., Tallarek, U., Influence of stagnant zones on transient and asymptotic dispersion in macroscopically homogeneous porous media (2002) Phys. Rev. Lett., 88 (23), p. 234501","Galvosas, P.; MacDiarmid Institute for Advanced Materials and Nanotechnology, School of Chemical and Physical Sciences, Victoria University of Wellington, Wellington 6001, New Zealand; email: petrik.galvosas@vuw.ac.nz",,,,,,,,10907807,,JMARF,,"English","J. Magn. Reson.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-84855376534
